  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6597.06 sitting just below the massive 6600 gamma wall (4.6B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 6600 as they hedge their long gamma position, creating strong resistance at that level. The PIN regime with stacked positive gamma from 6580-6610 suggests dealers will provide two-way flow to keep price rangebound, buying any dips toward 6590/6585 and selling rallies into 6600. Watch 6600 as the critical inflection point—any sustained break above triggers heavy dealer selling pressure, while a fade back toward 6590 should see dealer buying support kick in.",
